Analyzing WeRateDogs¶

WeRateDogs is a Twitter account that rates people's dogs with a humorous comment about the dog. These ratings almost always have a denominator of 10. The numerators, though? Almost always greater than 10. 11/10, 12/10, 13/10, etc. Why? Because "they're good dogs Brent." WeRateDogs has over 4 million followers and has received international media coverage. After, we gathered, assessed, and cleaned our datasets, here are the following analysis and visualizations.

Favorite count versus Retweet count¶

In [47]:
plt.figure(1, figsize = (8, 5))
plt.plot(df.favorite_count, df.retweet_count, marker='o', linestyle='', ms=2 )
plt.title('Favorite Count vs Retweet Count)'
plt.xscale('log')
plt.ylabel('Favorite Count')
plt.yscale('log')
plt.xlabel('Retweet Count')
plt.show();

We have a strong correlation between favorite and retweet count. This is not suprising. Anybody who has a twitter account could tell you how both numbers increase or decrease at the same time.

Overall, how many original tweets were posted per month?¶

In [53]:
tweets_per_month = df.groupby(['Month', 'Year'], 
                               sort=False).count().iloc[::-1, 0]
In [54]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots()
sns.set_style("white")
tweets_per_month.plot(kind='bar', color='b')
ax.set_title('Number of original tweets per month', fontsize=14, fontweight="bold")
ax.set_ylabel('Count', fontsize=12)
ax.set_xlabel('')
ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)

November and December of 2015 were the most busy months for WeRateDogs twitter account with the number of original posted tweets exceeding 250 and 350 respectively. From April 2016 and onwards no month had more than 100 tweets posted. This make sense because during these two months, we have Thanksgiving, chrismas and New Year's Eve holidays. A lot of people are on vacantion and spend more time with family and friends. So, reason why they have time to catch up with friens and family.
